description:
The ECUP escapes its crib, grabs a screwdriver and toddles toward the wall-socket, with 'The Legend of Kamui'!

Various manga sites say:

The rogue ninja Kamui is struggling to free himself from the iron fist of his own clan. As a ronin, he should not exist. In his flight from his clan he meets another ronin ninja, a woman named Sugaru. Sugaru, wanting only to live in peace, is very distrustful. Her paranoia is shown to be justified. The manga covers Kamui's struggle to leave his past behind and Sugaru's failure to do the same.

Written and penciled by Sanpei Shirato, Legend of Kamui was published bi-weekly by Eclipse (in partnership with Viz) in 1987-88 and ran for 37 issues. Along with Mai, the Psychic Girl and Area 88, Kamui was one of the first manga series translated for American audiences.

This torrent contains all 37 issues. Plaudits to the creator and the scanners! Score it, scatter it!



